[[Image:Phu Chee Fah.JPG|thumb|right|450px|View from [[Phu Chi Fa]] forest park, [[Chiang Rai Province]]]] '''Forest parks''' ({{lang-th|วนอุทยาน}}) in [[Thailand]] are [[protected area]]s set aside for conservation and protection from development owing to their natural scenic value that are too small to be declared [[List of national parks of Thailand|national parks]].<ref>[http://www.helsinki.fi/vitri/research/Educational_Projects/forrsa/RE_1_Proceedings/Forrsa_RE_1/RE_1_proceedings_pdf/Report_Gr4.pdf Natural Forest Management for Biodiversity Conservation in Thailand]</ref> The forest parks are governed by the [[Provinces of Thailand|provincial]] administrations. Thailand's forest parks fall under [[IUCN]] Category V, (Protected Landscape/Seascape).<ref>[http://www.iucn.org/about/work/programmes/pa/pa_products/wcpa_categories/pa_categoryv/ IUCN Category V - Protected Landscape/seascape Ecotourism Resources and Management in Thailand] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120330234012/http://www.iucn.org/about/work/programmes/pa/pa_products/wcpa_categories/pa_categoryv/ |date=2012-03-30 }}</ref> There are a total of 69 Forest Parks in Thailand, covering a combined land surface of 880 km², which is about a 0.17% of the total area of the country.<ref>[http://conservation.forest.ku.ac.th/ecotourdb/Cgi-bin/ARTICLE/article_pdf/Ecotourism_re_mgt_Thailand.pdf Ecotourism Resources and Management in Thailand] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140801115027/http://conservation.forest.ku.ac.th/ecotourdb/Cgi-bin/ARTICLE/article_pdf/Ecotourism_re_mgt_Thailand.pdf |date=2014-08-01 }}</ref>
Since the first protected area was established in Thailand, their capacity to achieve their purpose has been under multiple challenges. As other protected areas such as National Parks and Wildlife Reserves, forest parks are not free from severe threats such as [[land encroachment]], [[illegal logging]] and [[poaching]].<ref>[http://www.earthlore.ca/clients/WPC/English/grfx/sessions/PDFs/session_3/Emphandhu.pdf Thailand’s Experience in Protected Area Management]{{dead link|date=December 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> ==Forest parks of Thailand==
